# Marsh API (Backend)

The Express + MongoDB backend for Marsh. API-only — it serves no HTML. Pair it
with the **marsh-frontend** folder.

## Run locally

```bash
cd marsh-backend
npm install
cp .env.example .env     # then fill in the values
npm run dev              # starts on http://localhost:5000
```

Required env vars (see `.env.example`):

| Key                   | Notes                                            |
|-----------------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| `MONGODB_URI`         | MongoDB Atlas connection string                  |
| `JWT_SECRET`          | long random string                               |
| `SESSION_SECRET`      | long random string                               |
| `GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID`    | from Google Cloud Console                        |
| `GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET`| from Google Cloud Console                        |
| `CLIENT_ORIGIN`       | the frontend URL, e.g. `http://localhost:3000`   |

Generate a secret:
```bash
node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(48).toString('hex'))"
```

## Create the first admin

```bash
npm run seed:admin -- admin@example.com "Admin Name" StrongPass123
```
(Existing email → promoted to admin; new email → admin account created.)

## Deploy to Render

1. Push `marsh-backend` to its own GitHub repo (or a subfolder).
2. Render → **New → Web Service** (or **Blueprint** using the included `render.yaml`).
   - Build: `npm install`
   - Start: `node server.js`
   - Health check: `/api/health`
3. Set env vars in the dashboard. **`CLIENT_ORIGIN` must be your deployed
   frontend URL** (e.g. `https://marsh-frontend.onrender.com`), or CORS will
   block requests.

## How auth works across two origins

Because the frontend and backend are separate apps, the JWT is returned in the
login response body and stored by the frontend, then sent as
`Authorization: Bearer <token>`. A secure HTTP-only cookie is also set as
defense-in-depth. This is why login works in local dev even when browsers block
third-party cookies.

## API routes

| Method | Route                    | Auth        |
|--------|--------------------------|-------------|
| POST   | `/auth/google`           | public      |
| POST   | `/auth/login`            | public      |
| POST   | `/auth/logout`           | public      |
| GET    | `/api/user`              | user        |
| PUT    | `/api/user/update`       | user        |
| GET    | `/api/user/balance`      | user        |
| PUT    | `/api/user/balance`      | user        |
| GET    | `/api/admin/users`       | admin       |
| PUT    | `/api/admin/update-user` | admin       |
| DELETE | `/api/admin/user/:id`    | admin       |
| GET    | `/api/health`            | public      |
| GET    | `/api/csrf-token`        | public      |

All mutating requests require the `X-CSRF-Token` header (handled automatically
by the frontend).
